being bombarded by particles

01:00:10.840 --> 01:00:12.230
all the time.

01:00:12.230 --> 01:00:14.837
And especially they are
interesting because they're

01:00:14.837 --> 01:00:16.420
super, super-high
energy, like they're

01:00:16.420 --> 01:00:18.120
super-duper high energy.

01:00:18.120 --> 01:00:19.779
We're being shot at
by these particles.

01:00:19.779 --> 01:00:21.820
And nobody really knows
where they're coming from

01:00:21.820 --> 01:00:23.980
or what could be making them.

01:00:23.980 --> 01:00:26.140
Like, there's no
process in nature,

01:00:26.140 --> 01:00:30.250
or astrophysics, or physics that
scientists know about, or could

01:00:30.250 --> 01:00:33.460
even imagine, could be producing
these super-high energy

01:00:33.460 --> 01:00:34.730
particles.

01:00:34.730 --> 01:00:36.700
And so the possibilities
are, like, insane.

01:00:36.700 --> 01:00:39.310
Like, there could be
something totally new thing

01:00:39.310 --> 01:00:41.650
in the universe nobody
has ever seen before.

01:00:41.650 --> 01:00:43.530
Or it could be, like,
aliens shooting at us.

01:00:46.060 --> 01:00:48.194
So it's a pretty cool mystery.

01:00:58.919 --> 01:00:59.460
AUDIENCE: Hi.

