theory if we're expanding now?

01:01:10.560 --> 01:01:11.100
DANIEL WHITESON: Great question.

01:01:11.100 --> 01:01:11.670
Yeah.

01:01:11.670 --> 01:01:14.610
So there was a theory, the
sort of cyclical universe,

01:01:14.610 --> 01:01:18.030
Big Bang, Big Crunch,
Big Bang, Big Crunch.

01:01:18.030 --> 01:01:20.400
That theory is less popular
now because of dark energy.

01:01:20.400 --> 01:01:23.310
Because we know the universe
is expanding like crazy.

01:01:23.310 --> 01:01:27.014
But we don't know what dark
energy holds for the future.

01:01:27.014 --> 01:01:28.680
Dark energy, for
example, only turned on

01:01:28.680 --> 01:01:30.790
about 5 billion years ago.

01:01:30.790 --> 01:01:32.640
So for a long time,
the universe was just

01:01:32.640 --> 01:01:34.410
sort of coasting
and slowing down.

01:01:34.410 --> 01:01:35.327
And then it turned on.

01:01:35.327 --> 01:01:36.868
What's going to
happen in the future?

01:01:36.868 --> 01:01:38.760
It might turn around
and make a Big Crunch.

01:01:38.760 --> 01:01:40.890
So a Big Crunch is
still a possibility.

01:01:40.890 --> 01:01:43.950
In fact, there's a theory of
spacetime called loop quantum

01:01:43.950 --> 01:01:46.320
gravity, that says
that maybe all of space

01:01:46.320 --> 01:01:48.510
is pixelated on this
tiny, tiny scale.

01:01:48.510 --> 01:01:50.550
And it specifically
predicts a Big Crunch.

01:01:50.550 --> 01:01:53.070
So the short answer is a Big
Crunch might still happen,

01:01:53.070 --> 01:01:54.362
but nowhere in the near future.

01:01:54.362 --> 01:01:55.361
So don't worry about it.

01:01:55.361 --> 01:01:57.300
And you still have to
pay next year's taxes.

01:01:57.300 --> 01:01:59.220
[LAUGHTER]

01:01:59.220 --> 01:02:01.060
But we know dark energy
is such a mystery.

01:02:01.060 --> 01:02:02.700
We can't predict
what's going to happen

01:02:02.700 --> 01:02:05.033
because we don't understand
the mechanism for it at all.

