01:04:34.250 --> 01:04:35.150
AUDIENCE: Hello.

01:04:35.150 --> 01:04:39.230
Are there any questions that you
cannot conceive of a possible

01:04:39.230 --> 01:04:39.920
answer to?

01:04:39.920 --> 01:04:43.891
So with dark energy, you
could start making up theories

01:04:43.891 --> 01:04:44.390
tomorrow.

01:04:44.390 --> 01:04:46.556
And none of them would be
particularly well-founded.

01:04:46.556 --> 01:04:47.990
They'd likely be wrong.

01:04:47.990 --> 01:04:52.040
But it seems to me, like,
you can conceive of what

01:04:52.040 --> 01:04:54.514
the answer might look like.

01:04:54.514 --> 01:04:56.430
Are there any questions
where that's not true?

01:04:56.430 --> 01:05:00.322
So for me, one maybe
is consciousness.

01:05:00.322 --> 01:05:01.280
DANIEL WHITESON: Right.

01:05:01.280 --> 01:05:02.363
So that's a very question.

01:05:02.363 --> 01:05:06.190
A lot of the times
we can speculate.

01:05:06.190 --> 01:05:08.760
But our speculation exceeds
the bounds of science.

01:05:08.760 --> 01:05:12.186
So one example is what
happened before the Big Bang?

01:05:12.186 --> 01:05:14.310
Well, it may be that all
the information about what

01:05:14.310 --> 01:05:18.030
happened before the Big Bang
was destroyed in the Big Bang.

01:05:18.030 --> 01:05:20.460
We'll never know.

01:05:20.460 --> 01:05:22.669
One popular theory
of the Big Bang

01:05:22.669 --> 01:05:24.210
is that the Big Bang
was one of many.

01:05:24.210 --> 01:05:26.310
And is an infinite
number of universes

01:05:26.310 --> 01:05:29.391
that were all created, but now
are separated from each other,

01:05:29.391 --> 01:05:31.140
and are moving away
from each other faster

01:05:31.140 --> 01:05:32.140
than the speed of light.

01:05:32.140 --> 01:05:33.450
So we will never detect them.

01:05:33.450 --> 01:05:34.890
That kind of theory is fun.

01:05:34.890 --> 01:05:38.497
But it's basically philosophy
because you can't ever test it.

01:05:38.497 --> 01:05:40.080
So, yeah, there are
a lot of questions

01:05:40.080 --> 01:05:41.650
like what happened
before the Big Bang,

01:05:41.650 --> 01:05:43.191
where we can have
ideas, but it's not

01:05:43.191 --> 01:05:45.090
clear we'll ever be
able to test them.

01:05:45.090 --> 01:05:47.940
However, science is
always moving forward.

01:05:47.940 --> 01:05:50.815
And things that used to
be philosophy questions

01:05:50.815 --> 01:05:51.967
are now science questions.

01:05:51.967 --> 01:05:54.300
Because we've developed new
technologies, and new ideas,

01:05:54.300 --> 01:05:58.230
and new clever ways to
test these subtle theories.

01:05:58.230 --> 01:06:00.650
That question you raised,
what is consciousness,

01:06:00.650 --> 01:06:02.550
is sort of a
favorite one of mine.

01:06:02.550 --> 01:06:04.470
It's one that I think
will actually never

01:06:04.470 --> 01:06:09.150
be testable by science because
science assumes consciousness.

01:06:09.150 --> 01:06:12.300
And so you can never step
outside of it to probe that.

01:06:12.300 --> 01:06:14.527
But that's a whole other topic.

01:06:14.527 --> 01:06:16.475
That's a great question.

